---
import SectionHead from './SectionHead.astro';

const stats = [
  { k: '3+ yrs', v: 'shipping production code' },
  { k: '14+',    v: 'page custom Shopify themes' },
  { k: '400+',   v: 'SKUs migrated · normalized' },
  { k: '90+',    v: 'Lighthouse · -30% TTI' },
];
---

<section class="section" id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <SectionHead
      idx="03"
      kicker="// about"
      inlineDescr
      descr="3 years in code · 9 years sous chef · ships quality"
    />

    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-photo reveal">
        <div class="about-photo-chrome">
          <span>~/about.jpg</span>
          <span class="muted-3">portrait/02</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-photo-img">
          <img class="photo" src="/casey-about.jpg" alt="Casey Hsu portrait" width="1080" height="1620" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="about-text reveal">
        <h2>Nine years in <span class="accent">kitchens</span>, three in <span class="accent">code.</span> The discipline carries over.</h2>

        <div class="about-para">
          <p>
            Most of my work today is in <strong>Shopify</strong>, <strong>HubSpot CMS</strong>, and <strong>WordPress</strong> —
            with React/Next.js frontends and Node.js backends. The day-to-day is JavaScript, TypeScript, Docker, and modern AI-assisted workflows.
          </p>
          <p>
            Before tech, I spent nine years leading culinary teams. It taught me how to stay calm under pressure, communicate clearly, and deliver on deadlines.
            I'm a <strong>George Brown</strong> Computer Programming and Analysis honours grad and a <strong>Contentful Certified Professional</strong>.
          </p>
          <p class="muted">
            Currently open to full-time roles in the Greater Toronto Area, including hybrid and on-site opportunities.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="stats-strip">
          {stats.map((s) => (
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="k">{s.k}</div>
              <div class="v">{s.v}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
